         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>The Fǝkkāre malakot is a theological treatise transmitted in the codex unicus <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet119">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien 119</t:ref>
            together with <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1578hamara">Ḥamara nafs</t:ref>, <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1885Marsam">Mars ʾamin</t:ref> and <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2635Dawana">Ḍawana nafs</t:ref>. 
            It deals with the weakness of
         human understanding regarding the mystery of the Godhead and had been attributed to the za-Mikāʾelites, but is now considered to be the work of an Ethiopian Orthodox monophysite
         monastic milieu.</t:p>
            <t:p>
